title: Cyclones football pays visit to STAR Industries
text: slideshow It’s not every day the individuals working at STAR Industries get a visit from the Russellville Cyclones football team, but when they do, a pep rally breaks out.Cyclones first-year head coach Billy Dawson and members of the Russellville football team were greeted with a pep rally-like welcome as they entered STAR Industries on Friday. Team members toured the work center, talked with individuals about the type of work they did and provided opportunities.During the group shot of the team and Cyclones alumni the team and workers shouted together, “We are the Cyclones, yes, we are.”STAR Industries is a day program subsidiary of Friendship Community Care centered on empowering families and individuals who are navigating life with a disability.
